HEADWORD: Infare
<hw>In"fare`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>inf⟦ae⟧r</ets> entrance.]</ety> <def>A house-warming; especially, a
reception, party, or entertainment given by a newly married couple, or
by the husband upon receiving the wife to his house.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>infair</asp>.]</altsp> <mark>[Scot., & Local,
U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Infashionable</ent>⟦br⟧
